Hide stock VS Code surfaces via configurationDefaults (PRO-5559)

Adds five configurationDefaults keys to the workbench bootstrap so the
Profiles IDE matches the Figma reference (node 101-3202) without
extra source patches:

  - editor.minimap.enabled = false
  - breadcrumbs.enabled = false
  - editor.stickyScroll.enabled = false
  - telemetry.feedback.enabled = false (hides the feedback / issue
    reporter surfaces)
  - workbench.editor.editorActionsLocation = 'hidden' (hides the
    split-editor / more-actions icons on the right of the tab strip)

These keys live in `webClientServer.ts` alongside the other Profiles
configurationDefaults set by `getting-started.diff`. Splitting them
into a dedicated patch keeps the PRO-5559 intent separable from the
older PRO-5511 onboarding defaults and lets us drop / iterate them
without touching `getting-started.diff` (the user can still override
any of the keys via settings.json -- configurationDefaults are the
shipped defaults, not forced values).

